###############################################################################
# resilience-lab — 10: hubs e conexões (logistics-service :8082)
# Pré-requisito: perfil "local" — o HubDataSeeder semeia 5 hubs (Blumenau 89010000,
# Joinville 89201000, Florianópolis 88010000, Curitiba 80010000, São Paulo 01310100)
# e 5 conexões; o GET de listagem deve mostrá-los.
# IntelliJ: ambiente "lab" (requests/http-client.env.json). Execute de cima para baixo.
#
# Passos SQS-only do lab (eventos hub.* na hub-events-queue.fifo, dedup, poison)
# não são expressáveis em .http — ver scenarios/*.sh.
###############################################################################
@logisticsHost = http://localhost:8082

### [Feliz] Listar hubs (esperado: os 5 do seeder + os criados abaixo)
GET {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs

### [Feliz] Registrar um hub novo (cidade/estado resolvidos no ViaCEP — precisa de internet)
# @name labHubA
POST {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Hub Lab Itajai",
  "cep": "88301000"
}

> {% client.global.set("labHubAId", response.body.id); %}

### [Feliz] Buscar o hub criado por id
GET {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs/{{labHubAId}}

### Segundo hub, para a conexão
# @name labHubB
POST {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Hub Lab Brusque",
  "cep": "88350000"
}

> {% client.global.set("labHubBId", response.body.id); %}

### [Feliz] Registrar conexão (aresta bidirecional — basta registrar uma vez)
POST {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs/connections
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originHubId": "{{labHubAId}}",
  "destinationHubId": "{{labHubBId}}",
  "distanceKm": 35.0,
  "transitTimeHours": 1
}

### [Falha 400] Nome curto (< 3) e CEP inválido
POST {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "X", "cep": "abc" }

### [Falha 400] Conexão com distância negativa
POST {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs/connections
Content-Type: application/json

{ "originHubId": "{{labHubAId}}", "destinationHubId": "{{labHubBId}}", "distanceKm": -5, "transitTimeHours": 1 }

### [Falha 404] Conexão referenciando hub inexistente
POST {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs/connections
Content-Type: application/json

{ "originHubId": "hub-que-nao-existe", "destinationHubId": "{{labHubBId}}", "distanceKm": 10, "transitTimeHours": 1 }

### [Falha 404] Hub inexistente
GET {{logisticsHost}}/api/v1/hubs/hub-inexistente
